# Lessons learned (don't relearn the hard way)

When you figure out a tricky, non-obvious **technical** problem (races, cache,
network, blocking, correctness), **append a short entry below** so it isn’t lost.
Skip obvious UI polish (colors, icon choice, spacing, copy). Format each as
**symptom → cause → fix** in 1–3 lines. Newest first. Keep it tight; prune duplicates.

## Lessons

- **Raw `(\frac{...})` inline math on screen.** Model `\(...\)` survived preprocess, then
  CommonMark escaped `\(`/`\)` to bare parens before `splitInlineMath` — MathText never
  ran. Also `looksLikeProseParenthetical` counted `\neq`/`\frac` letter-runs as English.
  Fix (#450): convert `\(...\)` → `$...$` in `protectMathEscapes`; strip `\\[a-zA-Z]+`
  before the prose-word count; wrap bare cmds outside existing `$` spans.
- **Chat “falls then snaps back” when stream ends.** Two bugs stacked: (1) intentional
  `STREAM_LAYOUT_SETTLE_MS` (280ms) hold before revealing full markdown/feedback/sources;
  (2) FlashList native autoscroll re-armed the instant streaming ended — same moment the
  row grows — so native snap hit the pre-growth height, then deferred JS `scrollToEnd`
  corrected again. Fix (#445): keep native autoscroll suppressed through that settle
  window too; one writer for the transition (JS), not two fighting.
- **Streaming math boxes flicker (blank → repaint).** Pending stream tail re-parsed
  every flush; `react-native-markdown-display` re-keys the tree so KaTeX WebViews in that
  tail remount. Short closed ` ```math ` / `$$` blocks sat under the 320-char settle
  threshold for many flushes. Fix (#443): `advanceStreamBlocks` eagerly cuts at the next
  safe blank line once a fence/`$$` has closed — don’t wait on char volume.
- **Chat cold start pulled Mermaid/Vega/MathJax.** Static imports from `RichFence` /
  `mathHtml` evaluated ~6MB of inlined vendors on every markdown message graph load.
  Fix: `React.lazy` Chart/Mermaid via `LazyHeavyRich`; MathJax in `mathHtmlMathjax`
  loaded only for multline/eqnarray when a WebView can mount.
- **Drawer menu needs many taps after Reanimated migrate.** Opaque left-edge hit strip
  (`zIndex` 210) sat on the hamburger; failed pan `onFinalize` also raced `settle(false)`
  against `open()`. Fix: `manualActivation` (claim only after horizontal move) + settle
  cancel only if the pan actually activated.
- **RNSVG “Codegen didn't run” flood.** Metro `resolveRequest` used Node `require.resolve('react-native-svg')` → `lib/commonjs`, skipping package.json `"react-native": "src/"`. Fabric babel codegen never ran. Dedupe via Metro's resolver with a pinned `originModulePath` instead.
- **Model toggles snap back mid-flip.** Controlled Switch waited on Auth context; racing
  bootstrap `updateMe({timezone|location}).then(setUser)` replaced the whole user with
  stale `enabled_models`. Fix: local draft prefs; `updateUser` generation guard; bootstrap
  merges only patched fields (`useBootstrapSync`).
- **Memory screen always waits on network.** Settings already `GET /memories` for the count,
  then `/memory` refetched from empty. Fix: shared `memoryListCache` (20s TTL + inflight
  dedupe); prefetch on Settings→Memory; hydrate on mount; invalidate on logout.
- **Header actions flicker while a chat is open.** `hasMessages={messages.length > 0}` drops
  the action group if the list briefly clears during load/refetch. Gate on
  `messages.length > 0 || routeChatId` so an active chat route keeps controls mounted.
- **iOS Simulator soft keyboard missing.** Host Connect Hardware Keyboard hides it.
  `defaults write com.apple.iphonesimulator ConnectHardwareKeyboard -bool false` (+ device
  prefs) and relaunch; ⌘K if needed. osascript cannot toggle Simulator without Accessibility.
- **TTS 502 ≠ API down.** OpenRouter 400: `openai/gpt-4o-mini-tts does not exist` → speech
  gateway Traceback + `/speech/tts` 502 while the rest of the API stays healthy. Fix the TTS
  model mapping; don’t restart the API for this.
- **WS ASGI Traceback on navigate.** `WebSocketDisconnect(1000)` while `chat_websocket` waits
  for auth JSON = client closed mid-reconnect; noisy, not a fatal server failure.
- **Image goes blurry/gray after the assistant replies.** Focus refetch after `streaming→false` replaces `local-*` ids with server UUIDs; id-only `mergeLocalAttachmentUris` dropped `local_image_uri` and restarted blur reveal. Also match orphaned local URIs onto incoming user attachment messages; user thumbs use `animatedReveal={false}`.
- **Attachment send showed `[BEGIN UNTRUSTED…]` + blurry spinner.** `wrap_untrusted` was persisted into the user message; focus refetch then dropped `local_image_uri` so ChatMessageImage remounted on a remote auth URL. Persist plain `[Image:]`/`[File:]` only; merge local URIs on refetch; skip blur reveal for `file://`.
- **CodeQL poly-ReDoS not cleared by `collapse_ws` / length caps.** CodeQL ignores those as sanitizers; rewrite sinks to linear scans (`find` / digit parse). See `.cursor/skills/security-alert-pitfalls/SKILL.md`.
- **Dependabot on transitive npm (markdown-it@10, uuid@7).** Direct pins don't help — use `pnpm.overrides` + regenerate lock with `npx pnpm@9.15.9 install`. See security-alert-pitfalls skill.
- **Raw LaTeX + smashed prose in math bubbles.** `normalizeImplicitMath` re-wrapped `(excluded values: $x …$)` / `(e.g., … like $x^4$)` as `$…$$`, inventing a trailing `$$` that stole the next display-math opener — equations showed raw and Wait—prose became a MathBlock (italic, no spaces). Fix: skip parens that already contain `$` or look like English prose (2+ letter-words).
- **SecureStore Keychain “required entitlement isn’t present” on simulator.** Linker-signed/adhoc builds (`TeamIdentifier=not set`, no identities) get `errSecMissingEntitlement` (-34018) on `setItemAsync`. Don’t put non-secrets (list order) in SecureStore — use filesystem; catch SecureStore writes. Proper Keychain needs a local Apple signing identity + `expo run:ios` rebuild.
- **Quiz wrong-answer UX: hint only, no re-render.** User rejected re-asking the same MCQ
  after a miss. Prompts must not emit a new ```vocab_quiz on wrong; chips stay on the prior
  quiz message (`findActiveQuizMessageId`). Grade against `get_last_quiz_assistant`, not the
  hint-only last assistant.
- **Quiz answers “don’t register” (Today stays 0/x).** Causes: (1) nested `session.commit()` in
  `messages.create` / `apply_quiz_result` mid–turn_prep; (2) letter answer + missing `vocab_quiz`
  fence → grade `None` and `skip_memory_jobs` blocked background sync; (3) My Learning 20s stale
  cache. Fix: `commit=False` until one outer commit; don’t skip jobs when letter grade fails;
  force-refresh projects list/detail on focus; invalidate home after grade.
- **Unpushed local diffs cause real pain.** User runs other machines/simulators off `main` /
  remote — finish every change with commit + push (see `execution.mdc`); don't say done with
  local-only work.
- **User rejected “Recalled N memories” chip + assistant Show more/less.** Do not reintroduce —
  see `.cursor/rules/chat-ux-bans.mdc`. Code-block fold only; assistant body stays unfolded.
- **User rejected model-fallback / context-summarized chips** (`chat.model_fallback` raw key
  flashed in chat). Do not reintroduce — see chat-ux-bans §4.
- **`ERR_PNPM_LOCKFILE_CONFIG_MISMATCH` on patchedDependencies.** Regenerating `pnpm-lock.yaml`
  with pnpm 11 drops patch metadata while `package.json` still declares patches; CI uses pnpm 9 and
  fails frozen install. Regenerate with `npx pnpm@9.15.9 install` (or pin `"packageManager"`).
- **Simulator can't reach LAN API URL.** Physical device needs `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://<lan-ip>:8000`
  (`./scripts/set-lan-ip.sh`); iOS Simulator needs `http://127.0.0.1:8000` (`./scripts/set-sim-ip.sh`
  or `./scripts/dev.sh mobile-sim`). Wrong URL → login/chat fails with network errors, not a code bug.
- **"Coverage is failing" but really lint/types are.** CI order is `ruff check → ruff format
  --check → mypy → pytest --cov-fail-under=80`; an earlier step failing means pytest never runs.
  Run the whole chain locally before committing, not just pytest.
- **Unpinned dev tooling silently breaks CI.** `mypy`/`ruff` were `>=`, so CI pulled a newer,
  stricter mypy and failed. Keep them capped in `pyproject.toml` and pin Python (`<3.14`).
- **SQLAlchemy `.rowcount` fails mypy.** `await session.execute(delete(...))` is typed `Result`
  (no `.rowcount`) → `cast(CursorResult[Any], await session.execute(...))`. Also never
  `from sqlalchemy import update` in a repo that defines its own `update()` (F811 shadow → wrong
  symbol at type-check).
- **mypy won't narrow a doubled `.get()`.** `usage.get("x") if usage.get("x") is not None else …`
  stays `int | None`. Assign to a local first, then branch on the local.
- **HTML/JS WebView preview "not working" = wrong build, not a bug.** `react-native-webview` is a
  native module; it never works in Expo Go. Rebuild the dev client (`pnpm expo run:ios`). It
  falls back to static HTML (scripts stripped) otherwise.
- **System dark mode on a static `C` palette.** Keep `C` (light) for unmigrated screens; add
  `useTheme()` and convert module-level `StyleSheet.create` into `makeX(t: Theme)` factories
  called via `useMemo`. Low-churn and incremental.
- **Mobile deps won't install in this env.** npm points at an auth-gated internal registry, so
  `tsc`/Expo can't run here — verify mobile changes with `pnpm typecheck`/`pnpm lint` locally.
- **expo-av / voice crash (`ExponentAV` not found).** `expo-av` is incompatible with SDK 56 — use
  `expo-audio` instead; lazy-load via `lib/voiceAudio.ts` for Expo Go; rebuild dev client with
  `pnpm expo run:ios` (not Expo Go).
